{
  "answer": "**In \"The Wife's Lament\" (chapter 3 of *Old English Elegies*), the speaker names her dwelling-place in the following passage:**\n\n> I was bid to dwell in a wooded grove,  \n> under an oak tree **in this earth-cave**.[^1]\n\nShe refers to it explicitly as \"**this earth-cave**\" (*eorðscræfe* in the original Old English), describing her forced isolation there amid hills, valleys, and overgrown briars.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Unknown, *Old English Elegies*, ch. 3 [paragraph](/works/unknown-old-english-elegies-d5fe9e/03-ik-this-giedd-wreche-bi-me-ful-geomorre/translation/#p-c1cc32).",
